                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d904">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/729: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-24T14:00:00-05:45"
                            >December 24, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 25—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>247. Department’s telegram 132, December 22, 11 a.m. President <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName> has submitted the basic law for the
                    Guardia Nacional to Congress. The latter has adjourned for the holidays and it
                    is improbable that the project will be acted upon until after the inauguration
                    of Dr. <persName corresp="#p_SJB2">Sacasa</persName> on January 1st.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
